node.title: Man facing wounding with intent charge over baby's injuries
node.description: Police arrest a man over the injuries suffered by a three-month-old baby who was admitted to hospital in Gisborne on New Year's Eve.
node.content:
["Police in Gisborne have arrested a man over the injuries suffered by a three-month-old baby who was admitted to hospital on New Year's Eve.", "", "
File pic Photo: 123RF
", "The baby was taken to Gisborne Hospital with critical injuries at around 10.30am on 31 December.", "The baby was later transferred to Starship Hospital in Auckland.", "After receiving critical care while at Starship the baby was flown back to Gisborne last Thursday and re-admitted to hospital in an improved condition, police said in a statement.", "A 24-year-old man has been charged with wounding with intent to cause grievous bodily harm.", "He will appear in the Gisborne District Court on Wednesday."]
